                        336
337 338 339 340 341 342 343
344 345 346 347 348 349 350
351 352 353 354 355 356 357
358 359 360 361 362 363 364
365 366
  </pre>
</p>



<p>The new version of cal is <code>ncal</code>.  It transposes the calendar (days run down the side) and can feel cramped, but it can fit more across a screen.</p>

<p>
  <h4>Without arguments, <code>ncal</code> shows the current month.</h4>
  <pre>
$ ncal
    September 2013
Mo     2  9 16 23 30
Tu     3 10 17 24
We     4 11 18 25
Th     5 12 19 26
Fr     6 13 20 27
Sa     7 14 21 28
Su  1  8 15 22 29
  </pre>

</p>
